80
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:16,880
by Qiong Qi.

81
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,080
Veggie!

82
00:08:43,048 --> 00:08:45,758
My poor Veggie!

83
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,320
How you've suffered.

84
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,280
Just 2 days,

85
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,120
and you've been cooked into a dish.

86
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,320
These soulless short-lived
Heaven Immortals!

87
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,640
What a sin!

88
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,920
This Veggie...

89
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,560
who are you talking about?

90
00:09:04,785 --> 00:09:05,825
Have you forgotten?

91
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,800
The field by the Water Mirror,

92
00:09:08,072 --> 00:09:09,912
the lover of the chives sister,

93
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,360
little Chinese flowering cabbage.

94
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:14,280
When you were young,
he used to praise you for your wits.

95
00:09:14,336 --> 00:09:15,376
Have you forgotten?

96
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:18,120
Well, at a glance,
it does look a little familiar.

97
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:21,040
But how could you tell?

98
00:09:21,232 --> 00:09:22,445
Of course I could.

99
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,931
It's Veggie!

100
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,737
Veggie has always had green leaves.

101
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,944
White stalks.

102
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,430
Rounded head.

103
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,760
Tender in texture.

104
00:09:31,865 --> 00:09:33,395
Of course it's him.

105
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,600
Don't all Chinese flowering cabbages
look like that?

106
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,417
Your Highness,

107
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,236
Your Highness,

108
00:09:42,289 --> 00:09:44,830
I heard you had a vicious battle at
Southern Heavenly Gates with Qiong Qi.

109
00:09:44,832 --> 00:09:45,832
Were you hurt?

110
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:47,139
It was nothing major.

111
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,364
Go on down.

112
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,640
Yes.

113
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:52,520
- Stop crying.
- Hello, Uncle.

114
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,015
Xu Feng.

115
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,600
This is...

116
00:09:56,961 --> 00:09:59,041
A rotten tree cannot bear good fruit.

117
00:09:59,184 --> 00:10:01,344
None of you Heaven-kind
have a kind soul.

118
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,960
Like father, like mother,

119
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,760
like son.

120
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,592
Xu Feng,

121
00:10:09,824 --> 00:10:10,904
do you still remember...

122
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,390
when you secretly
set free the Jade Rabbit,

123
00:10:12,392 --> 00:10:13,566
there was a Carrot Fairy...

124
00:10:13,591 --> 00:10:15,751
that was thrust around through
the Heavenly Palace?

125
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,767
Well, he's the one.

126
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,520
I was young and oblivious.

127
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,640
For the wrong that I've done onto you,

128
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,520
I hereby apologize.

129
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:26,800
But,

130
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:29,623
Heavenly Emperor and Heavenly Empress
are rulers of the six realms...

131
00:10:29,625 --> 00:10:32,382
They are not someone who can be
criticized by a petty fairy like you.

132
00:10:32,948 --> 00:10:34,040
Mr. Hu.

133
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,160
Let's all get along peacefully.
Speak nicely.

134
00:10:37,883 --> 00:10:40,224
Your dishes here are
the least bit tasty.

135
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,440
Little one,

136
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,811
follow me back to the Water Mirror.

137
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:44,743
And debrief to the fellow Floral Fairies.

138
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:45,918
I recently heard that
the Floral Realm...

139
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,318
had a fall out with the bird tribe...

140
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,720
for a mere fairy.

141
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,080
Is this uproar...

142
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,160
due to Jin Mi?

143
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,800
So what if is?

144
00:10:53,912 --> 00:10:55,432
What if it's not?

145
00:10:56,193 --> 00:10:57,310
The Floral and Heaven Realm...

146
00:10:57,312 --> 00:10:58,638
haven't communicated
for thousands of years.

147
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,760
Yet today, the Floral Fairies have to
attend to this personally...

148
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:03,516
for just a fairy.

149
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:06,232
Seems like there'll be lots
to weather in the coming days.

150
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:09,680
The Floral Realm
is none of your business.

151
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:11,000
Are you going back for this?

152
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,400
Very well.

153
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,120
Qiong Qi is causing havoc.

154
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,545
Father has sent me to
patrol the Demon Realm.

155
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:22,680
I'll leave tomorrow.

156
00:11:22,785 --> 00:11:24,265
I'll be gone for a good few years.

157
00:11:24,384 --> 00:11:26,676
If you stayed in Heaven,
with no one to train you.

158
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,920
It'd be a waste of time anyway.
Better yet to go back.

159
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,244
Phoenix, you fool!

160
00:11:30,383 --> 00:11:32,143
How can you let Jin Mi go?

161
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,000
That's great!

162
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,360
Now that we've bid farewell.

163
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,240
Let's go then.

164
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,351
Wait a minute.

165
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:44,135
Now... now's not the time to leave yet.

166
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:46,360
Why... why's that?

167
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,816
I've not done packing my bags.

168
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:52,440
Jin Mi, how are you more
clutter-brained than me?

169
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:53,800
You're no ordinary human.

170
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,400
What bags do you need?

171
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:57,280
Whatever pretty clothes you desire,

172
00:11:57,346 --> 00:11:58,640
you need only snap your fingers,

173
00:11:58,673 --> 00:12:00,000
and you have everything you need.

174
00:12:00,031 --> 00:12:02,280
I... I...
It's not clothes that I want.

175
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,800
It's... it's books that
I want to take along.

176
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,007
Books?

177
00:12:06,071 --> 00:12:07,087
Yes, yes.

178
00:12:07,776 --> 00:12:09,696
Since... since I came here,

179
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,880
I've been studying this
mental cultivation.

180
00:12:11,928 --> 00:12:14,833
There's a few chapters of scripture...

181
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:15,920
that I've not understood.

182
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,440
So I'd like to take them back,

183
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:19,751
so that I can ask Chief Peony,
isn't that good?

184
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,357
Your Highness,
Can I...

185
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:27,440
Can I take a few books
from your study?

186
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:29,830
I am truly glad,

187
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,440
that you have a
curious heart to learn.

188
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,760
The books in the study
are yours to take.

189
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,080
Thank you, Your Highness.

190
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,200
That's more like it.

191
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:41,280
You've finally matured.

192
00:12:41,536 --> 00:12:44,056
Little one,
besides just playing a fool,

193
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,600
you now yearn self-improvement.

194
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:48,480
Very well. We shall
leave tomorrow then.

195
00:12:48,806 --> 00:12:49,846
We shall leave tomorrow.

196
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:51,175
All right.

197
00:12:51,239 --> 00:12:52,358
- We'll leave tomorrow.
- Take more books.

198
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:54,160
Take more books.
Don't worry about the weight.

199
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:57,440
- If it's heavy, I'll help you.
- All right, all right.

200
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,920
Wait a while.

201
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,918
That should do it.

202
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,640
You've finally learn
not to feed me scalding water.

203
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,960
Qiong Qi was so scary today,

204
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:36,000
thanks for saving me.

205
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:38,360
Thank goodness, you are grateful.

206
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,120
I very much appreciate being alive.

207
00:13:40,191 --> 00:13:41,391
So I must give thanks,

208
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:42,720
for being my saviour.

209
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:46,240
I wonder how she plans to thank me.

210
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:59,129
How are you going to thank me?

211
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:01,280
Didn't I just thank you?

212
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,119
Forget it.

213
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,960
It's like I'm serenading a cow.

214
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,535
We were doing fine,

215
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:11,240
yet he suddenly gets mad at me?

216
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:12,760
What ridiculous mood swings.

217
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,080
Rest assured,

218
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:15,760
I will definitely defeat Qiong Qi...

219
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,040
and avenge you.

220
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,600
If you really do defeat him,

221
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:21,880
even if you
make me gardener then,

222
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,160
I'd be more than willing.

223
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:26,240
I'd even plant
a whole garden with Phoenix Flower.

224
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,856
What's the matter?

225
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:35,873
Are you all right?

226
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,080
Help me up over there.

227
00:14:38,535 --> 00:14:39,535
Yes, of course.

228
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,989
Slowly.

229
00:14:46,993 --> 00:14:48,059
Phoenix.

230
00:14:48,784 --> 00:14:49,904
Are you okay?

231
00:14:51,392 --> 00:14:52,392
I'm fine.

232
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,621
I'll be okay, with just a
change of luck after 12 days.

233
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:44,000
- Phoenix.
- No big deal.

234
00:15:48,432 --> 00:15:49,752
What's with that face?

235
00:15:50,056 --> 00:15:52,016
Your brows and eyes
are all scrunched up.

236
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,840
I was just thinking,

237
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:56,120
you're not using your powers
to stay strong, right?

238
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:58,520
Why would I stay strong for?

239
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:01,040
Then, get up and walk 2 rounds for me.

240
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,406
I'm up.

241
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:11,960
Not enough.

242
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:14,600
This can't determine
if you're really okay.

243
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,040
I must see for myself.

244
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:17,953
What are you doing?

245
00:16:18,025 --> 00:16:19,840
I want to see
if your back is recovered.

246
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:21,400
How would I know if I don't check?

247
00:16:21,825 --> 00:16:23,225
- Let go.
- No.

248
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:24,403
Let me see.

249
00:16:24,472 --> 00:16:26,550
Qiong Qi is so strong.
No way you'd recover so easily.

250
00:16:26,552 --> 00:16:28,352
If I don't see it myself,
I won't believe it.

251
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:31,295
If I say I'm fine, I'm fine.
Tugging and pulling, what a mess.

252
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:33,400
Let me see.
I'll stop once I see.

253
00:16:37,248 --> 00:16:38,248
Let me see.

254
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,480
Even immortals have scars too.

255
00:16:46,264 --> 00:16:48,104
Why do you have so many?

256
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,360
What happened here?

257
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,240
They were from former battles.

258
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:55,890
How long do you plan to keep looking?

259
00:16:56,863 --> 00:16:57,983
Fine, fine.

260
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,800
Do you all wild fairies...

261
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,400
know no bounds between men and women?

262
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:09,160
And always tug at people's clothes?

263
00:17:14,519 --> 00:17:15,679
It's fine that it's me.

264
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,400
But you can never
tug on other people's clothes.

265
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,000
Understood?

266
00:17:21,057 --> 00:17:22,057
Understood.

267
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,160
You're amazing.

